The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves attention mechanisms and learning pose-invariant representations, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The datasets used in the experiments are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
